cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with tree-to-word transducers, which are a type of automata used in language theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a partial normal form that characterizes the languages produced by linear tree-to-word transducers, which can be seen as a data structure. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper may involve logical reasoning in proving the decidability of equivalence of linear tree-to-word transducers. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with transformations of documents, which can be seen as a type of information processing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of deciding equivalence of linear tree-to-word transducers.
